      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Pastry, blind bake",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Rub the cold {{unsalted-butter}} into the {{plain-flour}}, {{caster-sugar}} and {{sea-salt-fine}}. Bind with the yolk of the {{eggs}} and {{water}}. Chill 30 minutes. Heat oven to 180°C fan. Roll, line a 23 cm tart tin, trim and prick. Blind-bake with baking beans for 12 minutes, remove paper and beans and bake another 5 minutes.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Frangipane, layer up",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Beat the softened second {{unsalted-butter}} with the second {{caster-sugar}} until creamed. Beat in the two {{eggs}} one at a time. Fold in the {{almond-flour}}, second {{plain-flour}} and {{almond-extract}}, this is the ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "frangipane",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmp879dw00000e8v41khfu2ev"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": ". Spread the {{raspberry-jam}} over the warm pastry base. Spoon the frangipane over the jam and level. Press the halved {{glace-cherries}} cut-side-up across the top. Scatter the {{almonds-flaked}}.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake, 30 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Bake for 25 to 30 minutes; the frangipane should be deep gold, set in the centre, and a skewer should come out clean. Cool fully in the tin before slicing.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
